  <refsynopsisdiv>
<synopsis format="linespecific">#include &lt;openssl/ssl.h&gt;</synopsis>
<synopsis format="linespecific">SSL_CONF_CTX *SSL_CONF_CTX_new(void);
void SSL_CONF_CTX_free(SSL_CONF_CTX *cctx);</synopsis>
  </refsynopsisdiv>
  <refsection xml:id="sources.openssl.doc.ssl.SSL_CONF_CTX_new.pod:DESCRIPTION"><title>DESCRIPTION</title>
    <para>
      The function SSL_CONF_CTX_new() allocates and initialises an
      <emphasis role="bold">SSL_CONF_CTX</emphasis> structure for use with
      the SSL_CONF functions.
    </para>
    <para>
      The function SSL_CONF_CTX_free() frees up the context <emphasis role="bold">cctx</emphasis>. If <emphasis role="bold">cctx</emphasis>
      is NULL nothing is done.
    </para>
  </refsection>
  <refsection xml:id="sources.openssl.doc.ssl.SSL_CONF_CTX_new.pod:RETURN_VALUES"><title>RETURN VALUES</title>
    <para>
      SSL_CONF_CTX_new() returns either the newly allocated <emphasis role="bold">SSL_CONF_CTX</emphasis> structure or <emphasis role="bold">NULL</emphasis> if an error occurs.
    </para>
    <para>
      SSL_CONF_CTX_free() does not return a value.
    </para>
  </refsection>
